	VALUES ('tt0022100', 'M', 'When the police in a German city are unable to catch a child-murderer, other criminals join in the manhunt.', '[Peter Lorre, Ellen Widmann, Inge Landgut]', 'Fritz Lang', '', '1931-08-31', '99 min', 92210, 8.4, 'In Germany, Hans Beckert is an unknown killer of girls. He whistles Edvard Grieg''s ''In The Hall of the Mountain King'', from the ''Peer Gynt'' Suite I Op. 46 while attracting the little girls for death. The police force pressed by the Minister give its best effort trying unsuccessfully to arrest the serial killer. The organized crime has great losses due to the intense search and siege of the police and decides to chase the murderer, with the support of the beggars association. They catch Hans and briefly judge him.', '[http://ia.media-imdb.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/small/unknown-1394846836._CB379391227_.png, http://ia.media-imdb.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/small/unknown-1394846836._CB379391227_.png, http://ia.media-imdb.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/small/unknown-1394846836._CB379391227_.png]', '[Crime, Drama, Thriller]', NULL, 'assets/img/tt0022100.jpg', 1931);
